Charles Judels https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Judels 0 Charles Judels (August 17, 1882 – February 14, 1969) was a Dutch-born American film actor. He appeared in 137 films between 1915 and 1949. He also did extensive work as a voice-over actor in animated films, including the voices of Stromboli and the evil coachman in Walt Disney's Pinocchio (1940), and in the Warner Brothers Looney Tunes short Porky's Garden (1937). He was born in Amsterdam, and died in San Francisco, California. Charles_Judels ( August_17_,_1882 – February_14_,_1969 ) was a_Dutch-born_American_film_actor .
